  "prompt": "How do you create foreign keys on a table by using phpMyAdmin?",
  "response": "Here's a step-by-step guide to creating foreign keys in phpMyAdmin:\n\n1. Open phpMyAdmin and select your database\n\n2. Open the table where you want to add a foreign key\n\n3. Go to the \"Structure\" tab\n\n4. Locate the column you want to set as a foreign key\n\n5. Click on the \"Index\" link next to that column\n\n6. In the \"Index\" dropdown, select \"Foreign Key\"\n\n7. Configure the foreign key details:\n   - Select the referenced table\n   - Select the referenced column\n   - Choose ON DELETE and ON UPDATE actions (optional)\n     - CASCADE\n     - SET NULL\n     - RESTRICT\n     - NO ACTION\n\n8. Click \"Go\" or \"Save\" to create the foreign key\n\nAlternative method:\n\n1. Open the table design view\n2. Click \"Relation view\"\n3. Choose the foreign key column\n4. Select the referenced table and column\n5. Set deletion and update rules\n6. Save changes\n\nSQL equivalent:\n```sql\nALTER TABLE child_table\nADD CONSTRAINT fk_name\nFOREIGN KEY (child_column)\nREFERENCES parent_table(parent_column)\nON DELETE CASCADE\nON UPDATE RESTRICT;\n```\n\nAdditional tips:\n- Ensure column types match\n- Referenced column should be a primary key\n- Foreign key adds referential integrity",
